24/01/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A two-day meeting of the defence ministers from the Adriatic Charter countries -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia -- began in Zagreb on Monday (24 January). 
Representatives of the United States and ambassadors of NATO member countries to Croatia are also on hand. 
The meeting is part of the regular communication established among the three countries in 2003 in an effort to join NATO.
In other news, the ruling Croatian Democratic Union (HDZ) announced the start of preparations for local elections, which will likely be held in mid-May. 
After a party session Saturday, HDZ leader and Prime Minister Ivo Sanader said that local branches of HDZ would independently choose nominees for mayoral and municipal council races. 
(Makfax - 23/01/05; Vecernji list, HINA - 22/01/05; HINA - 21/01/05)
